The paper deals with the concept of zone diagrams, which is a variation of Voronoi diagrams, and their existence and uniqueness in different metric spaces. This makes it likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of fixed point maps and equilibrium states, which are concepts related to dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also deals with the competition between sites for territory, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of normed spaces and smoothness of norms suggests that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) and mathematical physics (cs.MG) sub-categories.
